article.headline: Manhattan 89, North Dakota St 47
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Peter Mulligan scored 15 points, and C.J. Anderson had 14 to help Manhattan rout North Dakota State 89-47 on Wednesday night. With the victory, Manhattan coach Bobby Gonzalez improved to 100-56 in six seasons at the school. The Jaspers are 6-4 this season. The Jaspers sprinted to a 10-2 lead, with Mike Konovelchick capping the spurt with a dunk and a jumper. Manhattan used a 13-0 run to make it 33-8, and led 53-21 at the half. Konovelchick scored 13 points, Jason Wingate added 12, and Arturo Dubois had 11. Myron Green led North Dakota State with 16 points. The Bison (4-9) have lost five straight.
